title: GORGEOUS UPSCALE TOWNHOUSE
description: This upscale 2,106 sq. ft. townhouse was built in 1990, and has 2 floors w/full spacious private basement providing plenty of storage.

The 2nd floor has an oversized master bedroom (> 16' x 12') w/u-shaped walk-in closet, 2 additional smaller rooms, and a full bath w/jacuzzi tub & separate shower. The 1st floor has a large living room, coat closet, additional half bath w/washer & dryer built into one of the closets, and a fully applianced kitchen (Jenn-Air grill in center-island, fridge, double-oven, and dishwasher). The basement has an energy-efficient 2-zone gas heating system, is very spacious, open, dry, and clean. Smoke alarms are also hard-wired for additional safety. There's also a nicely landscaped backyard, 2 parking spaces directly in front of property, and off-street driveway parking available during parking bans. This property is excellent condition inside/outside and definitely a must see!

Safe and quite neighborhood with park/playground at end of street. Very pleasant and quiet long-term neighbors with Landlord close bye. Less than 3 miles from major hospitals (RI, Hasbro, W/I, Memorial, Miriam, St. Joseph's, Butler, Bradley), private schools (Brown, PC, J/W, Moses Brown, Lincoln, PCD, Bay View, Sacred Heart), shopping, gourmet restaurants, historic downtown Providence/Federal Hill and the East Side. Minutes from train stations to Boston and New York. Bus-line is only 1 block away.

There are No pets and No Smoking. Credit and criminal background checks required. This is a 24-month lease w/last month prepayment, plus security deposit. Lease price includes city Water, city Sewer, Landscaping, and normal city trash removal. According to the EP Housing Authority, this property is "not" eligible for Section 8. Based on past experience, this property has been ideal for faculty, professionals and/or small family. At $1,600/month, you can't find/beat this price-per-square-foot for similar quality/location. Email the owner today for an interview.
